<p>I've just uploaded the <a
 href="http://olea.org/paquetes-rpm/mono/">Moonlight RPMS for
Fedora</a>. I've
compiled and (lightly) tested them for the <a
 href="http://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Releases/10">10 release</a>.
Don't know about other versions.</p>
<p>For installing the plugin you only need to have configured <a
 href="http://olea.org/paquetes-rpm/olea-repo-release-0.0.2-1olea.noarch.rpm">my
repo</a> and then use:</p>
<pre class="code">[olea@lisergia ~]$ sudo yum install moonlight-plugin<br /></pre>
<p>You can test your instalation with the <a
 href="http://www.go-mono.com/moonlight/MoonlightStatus.aspx">websites
referenced</a> by the Mono Project. As expected it works with <a
 href="http://galeon.sourceforge.net/">Galeon</a>, <a
 href="http://projects.gnome.org/epiphany/">Epiphany</a>
and <a href="http://www.mozilla.com/firefox/">Firefox</a>.
If you find something to fix please <a href="mailto:ismael@olea.org">drop
me</a> a line.</p>
